<ext_description linkend="Test_requirement_allocation_arm.Test_requirement_allocation">
<note> The text description for this Application Object has not been fully updated to agree with the EXPRESS.</note>

A <b>Test_requirement_allocation</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="Requirement_assignment:arm:Requirement_assignment_arm.Requirement_assignment"/> for which the <express_ref linkend="Unknown:arm:Unknown_arm.Ee_requirement_occurrence"/> has test characteristics. A <b>Test_requirement_allocation</b> is the relationship between the <express_ref linkend="Requirement_decomposition:arm:Requirement_decomposition_arm.Test_requirement_occurrence"/> and the <express_ref linkend="Product_version:arm:Product_version_arm.Product_version"/> to which the requirement is allocated.
The terminals of the product are related to either parametric data in an executable form or to data derived from experimental or theoretical measurements.
<note>
The structural split of allocation and requirement occurrence permits re-use of common test requirements and associated procedures over multiple products.
</note>
</ext_description>
